 be the solution to this optimization problem and let 
\begin_inset Formula $\payEnd^{*}\left(\se_{i},\pub_{i},\ubPriv\right)$
\end_inset

 be the optimized period 2 payoff.
 We can use the envelope theorem and the implict function theorem to derive
 expressions for the comparative statics of the offers and regulator payoffs
 with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $\se_{i}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\ubPriv_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\pub_{i}$
\end_inset

.
