\begin_inset Formula $\offer_{i}^{*}\left(\se_{i},\pub_{i},\Sigma,\ubPriv_{i}\right)<\ubPriv$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=0$
\end_inset

 and the upper bound does not influence our problem.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\offer_{i}^{*}\left(\se_{i},\pub_{i},\Sigma,\ubPriv_{i}\right)=\ubPriv_{i}$
